Team,

We're seeing elevated 503 errors from the API gateway starting at 07:48 UTC. Error rate is at 18%, up from baseline of 0.1%. Affecting all regions.

Initial hypothesis: the new rate-limiting config deployed last night may be too aggressive. I'm rolling back now.

Will update every 15 minutes.

Eve

From bob@techcorp.com Fri Jan 10 08:22:00 2025
From: Bob Martinez <bob@techcorp.com>
To: eve@techcorp.com, ops@techcorp.com
Subject: Re: Production incident — API gateway 503s
Date: Fri, 10 Jan 2025 08:22:00 -0500
Message-ID: <incident-002@techcorp.com>
In-Reply-To: <incident-001@techcorp.com>
References: <incident-001@techcorp.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8

Eve,

I checked the logs — you're right. The new rate limit was set to 50 req/min per IP but we have several enterprise customers who legitimately send 200+ req/min through server-to-server calls. Their IPs hit the limit instantly.

Rollback confirmed on my end. Error rate is dropping — at 4% now as of 08:19 UTC.

Corrective action: we need per-customer rate limit tiers, not a global cap. I'll create a ticket.

Bob

From eve@techcorp.com Fri Jan 10 08:45:00 2025
From: Eve Nakamura <eve@techcorp.com>
To: ops@techcorp.com, bob@techcorp.com
Subject: Re: Production incident — API gateway 503s — RESOLVED
Date: Fri, 10 Jan 2025 08:45:00 -0500
Message-ID: <incident-003@techcorp.com>
In-Reply-To: <incident-002@techcorp.com>
References: <incident-001@techcorp.com> <incident-002@techcorp.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=utf-8

All,

Incident resolved at 08:41 UTC. Total duration: 53 minutes. Error rate back to 0.1% baseline.

Root cause: rate limit config deployed in v2.14.1 used a flat 50 req/min cap without accounting for enterprise API clients. Fix: rolled back to v2.14.0.

Follow-up: Bob will implement per-tier rate limiting (ticket #2847). Post-mortem doc will be shared by EOD Monday.

Eve

